Design a highly futuristic, unique, and immersive developer portfolio website for a senior full-stack developer with 6+ years of experience.

The website should feel like a next-generation tech interface, inspired by cyberpunk, sci-fi dashboards, holographic UI, and AI control panels.

Visual Style

Dark-mode dominant with neon accents (electric blue, neon purple, cyan, magenta)

Glassmorphism + subtle neon glow

Animated gradients, glowing borders, soft reflections

Depth using parallax layers and 3D transforms

Smooth micro-interactions on hover, scroll, and click

Futuristic typography (monospace + geometric sans-serif)

Layout & UX

Non-traditional layout (not a typical portfolio grid)

Floating panels, modular cards, HUD-style sections

Scroll-based storytelling (sections animate into view)

Command-center vibe with status indicators, progress bars, and live stats

Interactive elements that respond to cursor movement

Sections to Include

Hero Section:

Animated intro with glitch or hologram effect

Tagline like “Building the Future with Code”

Dynamic background (particles, circuits, or data streams)

About Me:

Presented as a system profile or AI dossier

Timeline of 6 years of experience

Skills Matrix:

Interactive skill panels with animated proficiency indicators

Skills include:

HTML, CSS, JavaScript

PHP, MySQL

C, C++

Web Automation

Meta Ads

Browser Extensions

CAD

Microcontroller Programming (Arduino, ESP)

Projects / Labs:

Shown as “Experiments”, “Modules”, or “Deployments”

Hover reveals tech stack, role, and outcome

Automation & Hardware Section:

Highlight Arduino, ESP, CAD, and embedded systems

Visuals inspired by schematics and circuit diagrams

Contact Section:

Futuristic terminal-style contact form

Animated confirmation feedback

Technical Feel

Built using HTML, CSS, JavaScript with advanced animations

Optional PHP + MySQL for dynamic content

Emphasis on performance and clean architecture

Feels like a real product, not just a portfolio

Overall Mood

Innovative, elite, and forward-thinking

Feels like entering a developer’s digital command center

Designed to impress recruiters, clients, and tech founders instantly 